    "what_description": "Rubus londinensis is a species of thorny shrub that belongs to the family Rosaceae. It is characterized by its compound leaves with 3-5 leaflets, which are typically 1-3 cm long and elliptical in shape, with a serrated margin and a petiole up to 1 cm long. The shrub produces white flowers in May-June, which are followed by red-black berries that are edible and have 4-6 seeds. The plant grows up to 1.5 m tall and has a spread of 1-2 m, with a woody base and numerous thorns. Rubus londinensis is native to the British Isles and is often found growing in wet habitats, such as marshes and riverbanks.",
