    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Rubus londinensis are its antioxidant properties, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids that can neutralize free radicals and prevent oxidative stress. Its cardioprotective effects are due to the bioactive compounds such as saponins that can improve cardiovascular health by reducing lipid peroxidation and preventing the formation of atherosclerotic plaques. The plant also possesses antimicrobial properties, which are associated with the presence of volatile oils that can inhibit the growth of various pathogens, including bacteria and fungi. Additionally, Rubus londinensis has anti-inflammatory properties, which are mediated by the presence of polyphenols that can reduce inflammation by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Its analgesic properties are attributed to the presence of tannins that can reduce pain by inhibiting the production of pain-producing enzymes.",
