    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Rubus londinensis are derived from its leaves, stems, and fruits, and include rubus tea, which is made by infusing the plant material in hot water to create a flavonoid-rich liquid, rubus jam, which is a sweet preserve made from the fruit, rubus tincture, a concentrated liquid extract made by macerating the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol, rubus syrup, a sweetener made by dissolving the tincture in water, and rubus wine, a fermented beverage made from the fruit. Rubus tea has been traditionally used to treat digestive issues and as a remedy for fever. Rubus jam has been used as a topping for toast and as a sweetener in baking. Rubus tincture has been used to treat a range of health issues, including inflammation and infections. Rubus wine has been consumed for its antioxidant properties and as a treatment for various health conditions.",
